---
import Card from "@/components/landing/Card.astro";
---

<section id="what" class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 sm:py-24 lg:px-8">
	<div class="max-w-3xl">
		<h2>One command, many sources, a file you can play anywhere.</h2>
		<p class="text-muted-foreground mt-4 text-lg">
			Speekify reads from where your content already lives and writes a plain audio file.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
		<Card title="Many input sources">
			Inline text, stdin, local .txt/.md/.pdf files, readable URLs, and YouTube transcripts. Auto-detected.
		</Card>
		<Card title="Local synthesis">
			Audio is generated on your machine with Supertonic v3. No audio leaves your computer.
		</Card>
		<Card title="Multilingual">
			en, fr, de, es, it, pt, ja, ko, and more, plus na for language-agnostic synthesis. English input is
			auto-translated to French when you synthesize in French.
		</Card>
		<Card title="Voice control">
			10 built-in voices (M1–M5, F1–F5), custom Voice Builder JSON styles, plus speed and synthesis-step tuning.
		</Card>
		<Card title="MCP server">
			Expose Speekify as a tool so AI assistants can generate audio inside your automations.
		</Card>
		<Card title="Open source">MIT licensed. Read the code, file an issue, send a patch.</Card>
	</div>
</section>
